  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under cold running <strong>water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, combine the <strong>miso paste</strong>, <strong>gochujang paste</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>in a bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>samjang</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic</strong> lengthways</p><p>Trim, then finely slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop off the <strong>little gem lettuce root<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and separate the outer leaves and wash them thoroughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>pork belly</strong> into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a dry, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>pork belly strips </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 8 min on each side or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>crispy pork belly strips</strong> to <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and remove the pan from the heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until golden</p><p>Tip: The pan should be hot enough to cook the garlic in already!</p><p>Slice the <strong>pork belly strips</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/korean-pork-bbq-samgyeopsal/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>, <strong>sticky rice</strong>, <strong>crispy pork belly strips</strong>, <strong>samjang</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>in the middle of the table to serve</p><p>To eat, spread a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong> with some <strong>samjang</strong> and top with a spoonful of <strong>cooked rice</strong>,<strong> crispy pork belly</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>spring onion</strong></p><p>Fold them up into a wrap and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
